Sentencas: The effects of doping transition metal and rare-earth elements on the Mn1.5Co1.5O4 coating were investigated to improve the oxidation resistance and electrical conductivity of coating/steel.
Titulo: Promoting electric conductivity of MnCo spinel coating by doping transition metals (Cu, Fe) or rare-earth elements (La, Y) for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: The results show that transition metal improves the coating densification, and rare-earth element inhibits the formation of highly resistive Cr2O3 layers.
Titulo: Promoting electric conductivity of MnCo spinel coating by doping transition metals (Cu, Fe) or rare-earth elements (La, Y) for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: The modified coating increases the octahedral sites of variable valence ion concentration.
Titulo: Promoting electric conductivity of MnCo spinel coating by doping transition metals (Cu, Fe) or rare-earth elements (La, Y) for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect

Sentencas: The areaspecific resistance (ASR) of the modified coating is reduced by 2-3 times compared with that of the conventional MnCo coating.
Titulo: Promoting electric conductivity of MnCo spinel coating by doping transition metals (Cu, Fe) or rare-earth elements (La, Y) for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect
